# Lightning 3 / SolidTV — TV Framework Rules

Lightning 3 renderer via SolidTV (Solid-based wrapper). Requires `tv-platform-html5.mdc` alongside this file. **We do not use Blits** — never reference Blits APIs, patterns, or syntax.

## Build toolchain

| Bundler | Plugins | Notes |
|---------|---------|-------|
| **Vite** | `vite-plugin-solid`, `@vitejs/plugin-legacy` for ES5, `resolve.dedupe` for `solid-js` + `@lightningtv/solid` + `@lightningtv/solid/primitives` | Lightning 3 starter template uses Vite. ~12 KB gzipped runtime. Rolldown in Vite 8+. |

Clone starter: `npx degit lightning-tv/solid-starter-template my-app`

---

## Focus manager (`@lightningtv/solid`)

SolidTV includes a built-in focus manager via `useFocusManager` (from `@lightningtv/solid/primitives`). Call once at app root.

- **`useFocusManager(keyMap?, keyHoldOptions?)`** — Attaches `keydown` / `keyup` on `document`. Maps physical keys to logical events (`Left`, `Right`, `Up`, `Down`, `Enter`, `Back`, `Escape`, `Space`). Custom key maps via `userKeyMap`. Key hold with configurable threshold.
- **`activeElement`** — Solid signal tracking the focused `ElementNode`. Set via `setActiveElement(elm)` or `autofocus` prop.
- **Focus path** — Walks from focused node up through parents, calling `onFocus` / `onBlur` / `onFocusChanged`. Ancestor-aware (e.g. `Row` knows when a child gains focus).
- **Key propagation** — Capture → bubble along focus path. `onLeft`, `onRight`, `onUp`, `onDown`, `onEnter` return `true` to consume. `onCaptureLeft`, `onCaptureKey` for capture phase.
- **Throttling** — `Config.throttleInput` (global) and per-element `throttleInput`.
- **`Row` and `Column`** — Handle directional navigation and child selection automatically. `Row` responds to Left/Right; `Column` to Up/Down. Both manage `selected` index and call `scrollRow` / `scrollColumn`.
- **Scrolling modes** — `scroll` prop: `'always'` | `'none'` | `'edge'` | `'auto'` | `'center'` | `'bounded'`. Default transitions: 180ms horizontal, 300ms vertical.

### Additional primitives

`Virtual` / `VirtualGrid` (virtualized rendering), `Lazy` / `LazyImport` (deferred loading), `KeepAlive` (preserve state), `createFocusStack`, `useHold` (long-press), `withScrolling` (scroll math), `FPSCounter`, `Marquee`, `FadeInOut`, `Preserve`, `Suspense`, `Image`, `Visible`, `borderBox`, `useMouse`, `portal`, `router`, `createTag`, `createSpriteMap`, `createBlurredImage`.

Source: [github.com/lightning-tv/solid](https://github.com/lightning-tv/solid)

